{
  "texts": [
    "For the distributed ecosystem to work effectively, users would have to be able to issue dynamic queries across these databases and be able to retrieve the necessary subsets of data.",
    "And, in fact, FAIR states that data should be registered with an appropriate index (F4).",
    "NIF set up one of the first searches across neuroscience databases by creating an index over the contents of distributed databases.",
    "At its height, NIF queried over 200 data sources across biomedicine comprising over 8 million data records (Cachat et al., 2012).",
    "NIF used the NIFSTD to help mediate across the different vocabularies and relationships that were needed to link across databases."
  ]
}